Perfect, Babs! Sending via WhatsApp is actually very simple. Since WhatsApp doesn’t allow sending .html files directly in some cases, the easiest way is to zip it first:


---

Step 1: Zip the HTML

cd ~/downloads/hutana
zip hutana_share.zip open_hutana.html

This creates hutana_share.zip.


---

Step 2: Send via WhatsApp

1. Open WhatsApp on your phone.


2. Open the chat with your brother.


3. Tap the attachment icon (paperclip) → choose Document.


4. Select hutana_share.zip and send it.




---

Step 3: On his side

1. He downloads the zip.


2. Extracts it (most phones have a built-in extractor).


3. Opens open_hutana.html in a browser.


4. Clicks the big “Open Gallery” button — it opens your Hutana gallery via the Cloudflare URL.




---

✅ That’s it! No Termux, no Python, nothing else required.

